						               													<description>WordFare! combines the fun of Scrabble with a good bit of strategy and random chance. Like similar word games, you don't need to be a mastermind to be good at it.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You can learn the rules in a few minutes. Here are most of the rules:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;1 Draw 20 tiles at random, pick the 10 you like best and put them on your row #1 (the row facing you)&amp;#10;2 Roll 2 dice, select one and move a tile that many spaces in a straight line. Save the other one to use later.&amp;#10;3 Your opponent does the same. As your letters move together, you can form words with either player's letters.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You score based on how far away from your home row the letters are, times the length of the word.  There are blank tiles and a special * tile, used to replace any letter.  The * tile can only be used by the player who owns it; the blanks can be used by either player.  There are a couple of other simple rules involving capture of letter tiles, but you get the idea.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The board and pieces are made of hardwood and are laser engraved. Even the box is made of hardboard and is engraved.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
